original: Ljungström, Erik Olof Johannes, stadsläkare, Huskvarna, f. 3/2/96 i Huskvarna av kamrer Karl L. och Hulda Georgina Lundin. G. 28 m. Elsa Högbom. Barn: Ingrid f. 29, Gunnel 31, Helge 35, Gösta 36. — Stud:ex. i Jönköp. 14, med. kand. 19 o. med. lic. 26 i Upps. Läk. v. Me-devi brunnslas. 26, assist :läk. v. Upps. med. klin. s. å., v. pediatr. kHn. där 27, tjänsteläk. i Huskvarna sed. 27, stadsläkare sed. 47, skolläkare v. folksk. o. v. komm. mellansk. sed. 27, v. sam-realsk. sed. 31, marinläk. av första gr. i res. 39, verksläk.
translated: Ljungström, Erik Olof Johannes, city physician, Huskvarna, b. February 3, 1896 in Huskvarna, son of accountant Karl L. and Hulda Georgina Lundin. Married on the 28th with Elsa Högbom. Children: Ingrid b. 1929, Gunnel b. 1931, Helge b. 1935, Gösta b. 1936. — Graduated from Jönköping Gymnasium in 1914, bachelor of medicine in 1919 and licensed doctor in 1926 from Uppsala. Worked as a physician at Me-devi Spa in 1926, assistant doctor at Uppsala University Medical Clinic the same year, at the pediatric clinic there in 1927, service doctor in Huskvarna since 1927, city physician since 1947, school physician at elementary and middle schools since 1927, at vocational school since 1931, naval doctor of the first grade in the reserve since 1939, industrial doctor.
